				"string" : "# üü¶ STAGE 9.2 ‚Äî The FolkMemory Narrative\n\nThis is the literal story we will present in our GT Curriculum:\n\n> ‚ÄúImagine each SOM neuron is a small shard of memory living on a distributed network.\n> Every time a new pattern appears, it announces:\n> *‚ÄòHere is what the world looks like right now.‚Äô*\n>\n> The shard that best recognizes this pattern becomes the **authority**.\n> Its neighbors update themselves by **listening** to the authority‚Äôs trail:\n>\n> *‚ÄòAdjust a bit toward me‚Äîless so the farther away you are.‚Äô*\n>\n> Over time, the entire network self-organizes into a landscape of meaning: neighborhoods of shards come to represent consistent regions of the world.‚Äù\n\nThis is pure Ward.\n\nAnd it matches Kohonen‚Äôs narrative from SOM 2001 Sec. 3.1 (‚Äúqualitative introduction‚Äù) almost word-for-word:\nlocal, lateral, decentralized, stabilizing. \n"
