				"string" : "# üü¶ STAGE 9.5 ‚Äî Case Study Plan (What We Will Put Into the GT Book)\n\nThis will become a chapter in our curriculum:\n\n1. **Introduction:**\n   How SOM works in strict mathematical terms.\n\n2. **Mapping to FolkMemory:**\n   Each SOM concept translated to a distributed-system metaphor.\n\n3. **Interactive Animation:**\n   Visualize BMU, trails, neighborhood, updates.\n\n4. **Discussion:**\n   Why this analogy matters for distributed learning, topic maps, and knowledge infrastructures.\n\n5. **Exercises:**\n\n   * ‚ÄúChange the decay schedule‚Äîhow does the FolkMemory respond?‚Äù\n   * ‚ÄúBreak neighborhood links‚Äîdoes coherence fail?‚Äù\n   * ‚ÄúInject contradictory inputs‚Äîtrack how the network stabilizes.‚Äù\n"
