				"string" : "# üü¶ STAGE 9.6 ‚Äî Why This Works (Pedagogically)\n\nLearners often find SOM ‚Äúmathematically simple but conceptually opaque.‚Äù\nWard‚Äôs FolkMemory metaphor fixes that:\n\n* The network becomes a social organism, not a matrix of floats.\n* Ordering becomes the story of a distributed system achieving shared memory.\n* Neighborhood function = gossip radius.\n* Learning rate = trust weighting.\n* BMU = temporary expert.\n* Reference vectors = evolving folk knowledge.\n\nThis is extremely powerful for our GT curriculum.\n"
